I am not on the day shift today... right?
You are meeting up with Funahara Yuki and Minase Kaori at Akebonobashi Station at 11:00.
At 14:30, you start second shift duty at the Public Safety Bureau.
Oh, that is right.
What is your room preference today?
Victor Horta's Hotel Tassel.
Okay!
I will use the library as reference!
02: Those Capable
Your dietary intake yesterday was 2200 kilocalories in total.
The recommended amount for today's breakfast is 240 kilocalories.
I will have a 200 kilocalorie Chinese-flavored breakfast.
Certainly!
It was my very first day on the job...
Why me?
What did I do?
Today's weather will be morning clouds giving way to sunny skies.
There is a 0 chance of precipitation.
The anticipated group stress in the Shinjuku ward is Level 3.
I recommend taking a supplement to prevent mental contamination.
I guess this will do.
All right, see you later.
Take care!
So...
You messed up, huh?
Yeah... though I cannot give you the details
since I work for the Public Safety Bureau and all.
I do not know much about these things,
but what you did was not in violation of your duties, right?
I guess not.
Then you do not have to worry about it, right?
Besides, your Psycho-Pass is not that clouded either.
I guess that means you are not that bothered by it after all?
C'mon, do not be mean!
I did not get a wink of sleep last night.
I am surprised the Hue Check showed such a clear color for you, considering what you went through.
You do not give yourself much psychological care,
and yet you are such a mental beauty.
How do you stay so healthy?
Well...
Maybe I am just thick-skinned, you know?
God really is unfair.
You said it.
I-In any case...
It is not that I doubt the Sibyl System,
but I wonder if a career at the Public Safety Bureau is really right for me.
Jeez, you are lucky to even have the choice!
I know you like to speak without thinking, but that is pushing it even for you!
To start with, you were found to have an aptitude for jobs
at the Ministry of Economy and the Ministry of Technology,
and yet you rejected them both and picked the Public Safety Bureau, right?
The best I could do was C-rank scores across the board.
What is the problem?
You are good at blue-collar work.
I am a systems engineer, so my shoulders are always killing me.
Akane, you were an honor student who scored 700 points on the last exam.
You should be able to take on any job with ease, right?
Sorry.
I guess we went a little too far.
But I think that if anyone can pull off that job, it is you.
And not just because of the aptitude the System indicated.
As a friend, I know you will do well.
That which needs to be done is carried out by those capable of doing it.
Such is the grace bestowed upon mankind by Sibyl.
Just kidding.
Excuse me!
Is Analyst Karanomori Shion here?
Yeah, yeah.
Who are you?
I am Tsunemori Akane.
I have been assigned to the CID as of yesterday.
Oh!
You are the new Inspector who shot Shinya, are not you?
Wow...
You are a lot cuter than I thought.
That cute face of yours hides how daring you can be, though!
What happened?
Did Shinya grab your butt or something?
No.
Um...
I was told I should come to you to find out how he is doing.
Oh, that.
While I do have a physician's license,
can you believe that is all it took for the government to delegate employee health care to the Analysis Lab?
Sure, I may be a latent criminal too,
but that does not mean they can just slave drive me as much as they want, right?
R-Right...
Let us see.
Akane, was it?
If you are an Inspector, that puts you on the fast track at the Bureau, right?
Hurry up and become a high-ranking official so you can reform the system.
You can start by splashing out for a swimming pool and bar lounge at the CID.
I am counting on you!
Right, well..
How is Kougami's treatment going?
Oh, that is right.
Well, you scored a direct hit on his spinal cord,
so he is still out of commission.
It will be a little longer before he is able to stand, talk, or anything like that.
Of course, you would not be able to join him in bed right now, either.
If you just want to peek in on him, that would be okay.
What do you want to do?
W-Well, I would better not bother him.
If he spends today resting, the aftereffects should go away.
Come back tomorrow morning.
Okay.

Huh?
Um...
Hmm?
Excuse me, are there any other tablets?
Enforcer Kougami is using the spare equipment.
But, um...
Is not Kougami...
Ow!
That hurt...
Here.
Use this.
O-Okay.
Sorry for getting in late.
Oh?
You are on duty tonight, young lady?
Ah, yes.
It must be tough after what happened yesterday.
Well, let us hope that today's a little quieter
This is an elevated Area Stress Level warning.
A Psycho-Pass above the regulation value has been detected
inside Iko Gryce Hill in the Adachi ward.
Inspector on duty, please accompany the Enforcers to the site immediately.
And just when I was hoping today would be quiet...
Well, our shift just ended, so... good luck.
Would you like me to cover for Kougami?
No, that will not be necessary.
Let us get going, Ms. Inspector.
What?!
Drones have been watching the entrances to the mall since the warning was triggered.
They have not caught anyone yet.
In other words, whoever's elevating the Area Stress level is still in the mall.
Are we going to use Dominators?
We will have them delivered to us as a precaution.
but we probably will not need them.
Well then, shall we go?
Do you feel uncomfortable?
I thought your generation was used to playing with holo-suits on.
It feels a bit weird with my whole body as an Avatar.
It is okay, so let me see.
Oh, stop it.
Not a chance!
Oh, there is our man.
On the right, hiding behind the front column.
But...
How can you tell without even using a scanner?
A beast can sniff out another beast's scent.
Excuse me.
Could we please measure your Psycho-Pass?
Whoa...
It is looking pretty cloudy.
My assessment is that you require emergency therapy.
Please come with me.
What?
Why?
I have not done anything yet...
So you really can identify latent criminals?
With experience, you will intuitively know at first glance when someone is up to no good.
Committing crimes, or cracking down on them...
Either way, they are talents that deal with criminal behavior.
That is why my Crime Coefficient is so high.
Thanks to that, I am now treated like a hunting dog who gets all the dirty work.
In the end...
I was pretty useless in there, was not I?
No, you were quite helpful.
Enforcers cannot walk around outside without an accompanying Inspector.
But that is...
We talked about this, right?
After you bring Enforcers to the site,
all you need to do is keep an eye on them to make sure they do not slack off,
That is all you need to do.
In other words, you are telling me not to do anything, right?
Can I join you, Ms. Inspector?
Sure.
I thought you were already off duty today.
We Enforcers are prisoners, you know.
Even when we are off duty, there is nowhere else we can go besides the CID floor and our quarters.
Well, sorry about earlier.
I got kind of carried away.
As you can see, all the other women
who work here are scary as hell, so...
I am just glad that a cute girl like you joined the CID, Akane.
Oh, can I call you Akane?
Yeah, sure.
But hell, an Inspector with the Public Safety Bureau?
Crazy place to work, right?
Why here?
Do you think I am not suited for it?
After what happened yesterday, anyone would probably think that way.
Sibyl's Judgment of my job aptitude
exceeded the Bureau's employment standards, so here I am.
That is the thing I do not get.
If you passed the Bureau's standards,
you must have gotten a good ranking for other places too, right?
Could not you have picked a different job?
Yeah.
I got an A ranking for all thirteen ministries and agencies, not to mention six companies.
What?
S-Seriously?
Yeah.
But...
For all the other jobs, there were at least one or two people besides me
who got the same ranking.
I was the only one who got an A ranking for the Public Safety Bureau.
There were more than 500 students and I was the only one.
So I thought that there must have been something that only I could do at the Bureau.
If I went there, I thought I could find my purpose in life...
I thought I would be able to find out why I was born here and now.
Do you think I am wrong?
I do not know.
What makes you think that someone like me would have any idea?
You could become anything.
You could choose any kind of life.
You have even agonized over it, right?
That is incredible.
You are just like those people from the days before Sibyl was created.
Nowadays, the Sibyl System reads your talent
and tells you the way of living that will bring you the most happiness.
And yet, you are talking about your purpose in life?
The reason you were born?
I never even imagined there were people who stressed over things like that!
I was flagged in a Psycho-Pass test when I was five.
I have been a latent criminal ever since.
No possibility for rehabilitation through treatment.
That is why I am here now.
And I would much rather be one of the Bureau's hunting dogs
and take on assassination jobs than spend the rest of my life in an isolation facility.
That was the only choice I had.
I was not planning to be mean to you or anything,
but I changed my mind.
So I will ask you again.
Why did you become an Inspector?
I am so sorry!
You do not see many Inspectors who would apologize to an Enforcer.
I guess you are angry, right?
That was your decision.
I have no right to complain.
Was my decision wrong?
Did I just stand in everyone is way and put them in danger?
I have been an Enforcer for a long time.
The hunting dogs' behavior of following orders to take down prey with neither hesitation nor doubt
is ingrained in my hands.
I just followed that gun's orders,
and shot many latent criminals.
It was for the good of society, I told myself.
It was easier to just accept that logic without question,
and past a certain point I did not even think about it anymore.
I did not even think to look back at myself and what I was doing.
I was a fool.
Being a detective is not about bringing people down.
It is supposed to be about protecting people.
Kougami...
You decided what was right on your own.
You were able to put justice before your duty.
With a boss like you, I might be able to work as a detective, not just a dog.
Thank you very much!
You also do not see many Inspectors who would bow to an Enforcer.
If you had time to think about it with a level head,
you would have tried not to shoot her, right?
I do not know.
I did not hesitate at the time.
I thought I would die if I hesitated.
I thought, I do not want to die in a place like this.
I cannot die here, no matter what!
That one thought consumed me.
I have unfinished business to take care of.
There is something I have to settle no matter what!
Kougami!
So, you are saying that you made the right decision at the time?
Is that your conclusion, Inspector Tsunemori?
Yes.
Her Crime Coefficient was only temporarily elevated.
In fact, the therapy she is receiving after being taken into custody is going well,
and her Psycho-Pass is recovering.
Kougami, is there anything you want to say?
No.
Inspector Tsunemori fulfilled her duty.
That is all.
